<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="locale.php" src="/private/var/www/wordpress.staging/wp-includes/locale.php"><scope doc="Class that loads the calendar locale.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0" ilk="class" line="14" lineend="357" name="WP_Locale"><variable citdl="array" doc="Stores the translated strings for the full weekday names.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@var array&#10;@access private" line="22" name="weekday" /><variable citdl="array" doc="Stores the translated strings for the one character weekday names.&#10;&#10;There is a hack to make sure that Tuesday and Thursday, as well&#10;as Sunday and Saturday, don't conflict. See init() method for more.&#10;&#10;@see WP_Locale::init() for how to handle the hack.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@var array&#10;@access private" line="36" name="weekday_initial" /><variable citdl="array" doc="Stores the translated strings for the abbreviated weekday names.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@var array&#10;@access private" line="45" name="weekday_abbrev" /><variable citdl="array" doc="Stores the translated strings for the full month names.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@var array&#10;@access private" line="54" name="month" /><variable citdl="array" doc="Stores the translated strings for the abbreviated month names.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@var array&#10;@access private" line="63" name="month_abbrev" /><variable citdl="array" doc="Stores the translated strings for 'am' and 'pm'.&#10;&#10;Also the capitalized versions.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@var array&#10;@access private" line="74" name="meridiem" /><variable citdl="string" doc="The text direction of the locale language.&#10;&#10;Default is left to right 'ltr'.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@var string&#10;@access private" line="85" name="text_direction" /><scope doc="Sets up the translated strings and object properties.&#10;&#10;The method creates the translatable strings for various&#10;calendar elements. Which allows for specifying locale&#10;specific calendar names and text direction.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access private" ilk="function" line="97" lineend="191" name="init" signature="init()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="117" name="weekday_initial_" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="159" name="month_abbrev_" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="181" name="GLOBALS" /><variable line="159" name="month_" /><variable line="117" name="weekday_" /><variable citdl="__()" line="173" name="trans" /></scope><scope ilk="function" line="193" lineend="195" name="rtl_src_admin_notice" signature="rtl_src_admin_notice()" /><scope doc="Retrieve the full translated weekday word.&#10;&#10;Week starts on translated Sunday and can be fetched&#10;by using 0 (zero). So the week starts with 0 (zero)&#10;and ends on Saturday with is fetched by using 6 (six).&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param int $weekday_number 0 for Sunday through 6 Saturday&#10;@return string Full translated weekday" ilk="function" line="210" lineend="212" name="get_weekday" returns="string" signature="string get_weekday(int $weekday_number)"><variable citdl="int" ilk="argument" line="210" name="weekday_number" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve the translated weekday initial.&#10;&#10;The weekday initial is retrieved by the translated&#10;full weekday word. When translating the weekday initial&#10;pay attention to make sure that the starting letter does&#10;not conflict.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $weekday_name&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="228" lineend="230" name="get_weekday_initial" returns="string" signature="string get_weekday_initial(string $weekday_name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="228" name="weekday_name" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve the translated weekday abbreviation.&#10;&#10;The weekday abbreviation is retrieved by the translated&#10;full weekday word.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $weekday_name Full translated weekday word&#10;@return string Translated weekday abbreviation" ilk="function" line="244" lineend="246" name="get_weekday_abbrev" returns="string" signature="string get_weekday_abbrev(string $weekday_name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="244" name="weekday_name" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve the full translated month by month number.&#10;&#10;The $month_number parameter has to be a string&#10;because it must have the '0' in front of any number&#10;that is less than 10. Starts from '01' and ends at&#10;'12'.&#10;&#10;You can use an integer instead and it will add the&#10;'0' before the numbers less than 10 for you.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string|int $month_number '01' through '12'&#10;@return string Translated full month name" ilk="function" line="265" lineend="267" name="get_month" returns="string" signature="string get_month($month_number)"><variable ilk="argument" line="265" name="month_number" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve translated version of month abbreviation string.&#10;&#10;The $month_name parameter is expected to be the translated or&#10;translatable version of the month.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $month_name Translated month to get abbreviated version&#10;@return string Translated abbreviated month" ilk="function" line="281" lineend="283" name="get_month_abbrev" returns="string" signature="string get_month_abbrev(string $month_name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="281" name="month_name" /></scope><scope doc="Retrieve translated version of meridiem string.&#10;&#10;The $meridiem parameter is expected to not be translated.&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;@access public&#10;&#10;@param string $meridiem Either 'am', 'pm', 'AM', or 'PM'. Not translated version.&#10;@return string Translated version" ilk="function" line="296" lineend="298" name="get_meridiem" returns="string" signature="string get_meridiem(string $meridiem)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="296" name="meridiem" /></scope><scope doc="Global variables are deprecated. For backwards compatibility only.&#10;&#10;@deprecated For backwards compatibility only.&#10;@access private&#10;&#10;@since 2.1.0" ilk="function" line="308" lineend="314" name="register_globals" signature="register_globals()" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor which calls helper methods to set up object variables&#10;&#10;@uses WP_Locale::init()&#10;@uses WP_Locale::register_globals()&#10;@since 2.1.0&#10;&#10;@return WP_Locale" ilk="function" line="325" lineend="328" name="__construct" returns="WP_Locale" signature="WP_Locale __construct()" /><scope doc="Checks if current locale is RTL.&#10;&#10;@since 3.0.0&#10;@return bool Whether locale is RTL." ilk="function" line="336" lineend="338" name="is_rtl" returns="bool" signature="bool is_rtl()" /><scope doc="Register date/time format strings for general POT.&#10;&#10;Private, unused method to add some date/time formats translated&#10;on wp-admin/options-general.php to the general POT that would&#10;otherwise be added to the admin POT.&#10;&#10;@since 3.6.0" ilk="function" line="349" lineend="356" name="_strings_for_pot" signature="_strings_for_pot()" /></scope><scope doc="Checks if current locale is RTL.&#10;&#10;@since 3.0.0&#10;@return bool Whether locale is RTL." ilk="function" line="365" lineend="368" name="is_rtl" returns="bool" signature="bool is_rtl()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="366" name="wp_locale" /></scope></scope>